article.linkText: Drinnon helps St. Francis (Pa.) beat Robert Morris 68-57
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Ronnie Drinnon scored 17 points and grabbed 16 rebounds and St. Francis (Pa.) defeated Robert Morris 68-57 on Thursday. Ben Millaud-Meunier added 14 points, Basil Thompson 12 and Georgios Angelou 11 for the Red Flash (13-11, 9-4 Northeast), who won their fourth straight game after starting the day in a three-way tie for first in the conference. Rodney Pryor had 14 points and 10 rebounds for the Colonials (7-19, 5-8) with Billy Giles adding 11 points. The Red Flash was 9 of 19 for 47 percent from the arc to 4 of 21 (19 percent) for Robert Morris, which only went to the line four times, making three, while St. Francis made 15 of 16 free throws. Drinnon scored eight straight points in an 18-7 run for a 64-51 lead with 2:21 to go. Three-pointers by Thomas and Millaud-Meunier gave the Red Flash a 38-29 halftime lead.
